[SN]TITLE[SN]
Fire breaks out at disused primary school in Coatbridge

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A fire has broken out at a disused primary school in North Lanarkshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Firefighters were called to the former site of the Drumpark Primary School in Coatbridge Road, Coatbridge, at about 07:00.
The school - which caters for children with special needs - has since been relocated to Albert Road where it merged with Greenhill Primary School.
A thick plume of black smoke could be seen from the M8.
